that kind of demoralizes the player, kind of.

252
00:15:33,027 --> 00:15:38,390
belittles them for whatever reason and you're playing a game and the game's being snarky at you

253
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:43,192
while the UI is being snarky at you, not even the game, that's even worse.

254
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:47,214
You're being, yeah, some kind of, some menu is pissing you off.

255
00:15:47,214 --> 00:15:55,698
So these kind of things contribute to an overall bad experience, so therefore, ooh, bad UX.

256
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:02,064
Next one is called daily quote unquote rewards.

257
00:16:02,064 --> 00:16:05,946
So this is where just as you're about to leave an app,

258
00:16:05,946 --> 00:16:07,386
they will say, oh, you should log in tomorrow.

259
00:16:07,386 --> 00:16:11,148
And you might get this thing.

260
00:16:11,148 --> 00:16:13,909
It's like a 0.000003% chance of getting it.

261
00:16:13,909 --> 00:16:14,670
So you should totally try.

262
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:17,011
And then you log in every day hoping

263
00:16:17,011 --> 00:16:18,451
to get that one amazing item.

264
00:16:18,451 --> 00:16:19,252
And you just don't.

265
00:16:19,252 --> 00:16:23,634
That's basically dangling a carrot in front of your players

266
00:16:23,634 --> 00:16:25,394
and making them come back for more.

267
00:16:26,335 --> 00:16:28,676
the chances are really low.

268
00:16:28,676 --> 00:16:32,639
I mean, daily login bonuses is not a bad thing,

269
00:16:32,639 --> 00:16:33,980
but when you promise something

270
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:35,601
with such a low chance of reward,

271
00:16:35,601 --> 00:16:40,044
it's almost like you're giving them false hope.

272
00:16:40,044 --> 00:16:40,865
I sound like a scorned lover, I'm sorry.

273
00:16:40,865 --> 00:16:41,185
Right, next one.

274
00:16:41,185 --> 00:16:43,486
Oof, guilt-tripping notifications.

275
00:16:43,486 --> 00:16:43,867
This one.

276
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:55,244
I really, really hate these.

277
00:16:55,244 --> 00:16:58,886
This is why every time I download a new app or a new game,

278
00:16:58,886 --> 00:17:02,147
I instantly deny any notifications

279
00:17:02,147 --> 00:17:05,628
because you get stuff like this where like,

280
00:17:05,628 --> 00:17:08,009
oh, you know, that's the voice I'm imagining

281
00:17:08,009 --> 00:17:09,350
the notification to sound like,

282
00:17:09,350 --> 00:17:11,731
you're dying, when can you come back?

283
00:17:11,731 --> 00:17:13,452
I was like, oh my God, shut up.

284
00:17:13,452 --> 00:17:16,293
Yeah, I'm literally saying shut up to my own notifications.

285
00:17:17,628 --> 00:17:21,529
I know that they're supposed to remind you that the game is still going on and they're

286
00:17:21,529 --> 00:17:26,270
supposed to entice you to come back, but if they're being whiny and they're basically

287
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:33,492
making you feel bad for leaving them, that's almost as bad as those, again, email subscriptions

288
00:17:33,492 --> 00:17:37,333
that you unsubscribe from and then you go to the website and then there's like a sad

289
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:40,574
little owl that's like, oh, I'm going to die now because you unsubscribed.

290
00:17:40,574 --> 00:17:41,454
It's like, really?

291
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:46,842
Yeah, so it's things like that.

292
00:17:46,842 --> 00:17:48,984
Like, it's completely unnecessary to add grievances.

293
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:54,287
So next one is social validation and compliance.

294
00:17:54,287 --> 00:17:56,309
This one is basically using your own friends

295
00:17:56,309 --> 00:18:02,993
to peer pressure you into playing your game.

296
00:18:02,993 --> 00:18:09,077
So the element of having friends playing the same games

297
00:18:09,077 --> 00:18:10,037
does actually,

298
00:18:11,797 --> 00:18:13,698
make you come back to a game more often.

299
00:18:13,698 --> 00:18:14,458
There's a study for this,

300
00:18:14,458 --> 00:18:16,699
I can't really cite it right now because I forgot.

301
00:18:16,699 --> 00:18:19,400
But the one thing that shouldn't happen

302
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:22,822
is when you're pushing it so much

303
00:18:22,822 --> 00:18:27,465
when that person, your friend, probably doesn't even care.

304
00:18:27,465 --> 00:18:29,686
Like, they're kind of using,

305
00:18:29,686 --> 00:18:33,608
they're using people you know to coax you

306
00:18:33,608 --> 00:18:38,570
into getting, into going back into the game.

307
00:18:38,570 --> 00:18:40,992
And I think I just personally don't really like that.

308
00:18:43,788 --> 00:18:45,490
Right.

309
00:18:45,490 --> 00:18:48,232
So there are some ways of doing things.

310
00:18:48,232 --> 00:18:52,956
Like monetization isn't evil.

311
00:18:52,956 --> 00:18:56,098
In-app purchases is not evil, obviously,

312
00:18:56,098 --> 00:18:59,040
but there are ways to do it better

313
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:02,743
and not so annoying, I guess.

314
00:19:04,959 --> 00:19:07,521
So this one's a good one, which is called clear trade-offs.

315
00:19:07,521 --> 00:19:10,983
So these are two different examples.

316
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:14,766
But basically, you are giving choice to the player.

317
00:19:14,766 --> 00:19:17,448
They know exactly what's happening, and they have a choice,

318
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:21,631
and you are giving them control over what they want to do.

319
00:19:21,631 --> 00:19:24,573
Do you want them, if your game is good enough,

320
00:19:24,573 --> 00:19:27,335
and they're enjoying it, they probably wouldn't mind

321
00:19:27,335 --> 00:19:31,258
watching that 30-second ad without you pushing it to them.

322
00:19:31,258 --> 00:19:32,899
I mean, I'm pretty sure, I've done it myself.

323
00:19:33,427 --> 00:19:35,609
I know a lot of other people have.

324
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:37,570
And the fact that they've actually let me say,

325
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:41,173
nope, I really don't want to watch this right now.

326
00:19:41,173 --> 00:19:42,694
I just want to continue playing something else.

327
00:19:42,694 --> 00:19:48,879
The same with a paywall where you buy once and that's it.

328
00:19:48,879 --> 00:19:50,100
No more ads forever.

329
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,842
So that's also one of my favorites because you know what?

330
00:19:52,842 --> 00:19:54,983
If your game is so good, I don't want ads,

331
00:19:54,983 --> 00:19:56,304
I will give you the money.

332
00:19:56,304 --> 00:19:57,685
Just don't bombard me with things.

333
00:19:57,685 --> 00:20:01,148
Again, this is about giving the player control.

334
00:20:03,793 --> 00:20:06,216
Next one is balance UI design.

335
00:20:06,216 --> 00:20:10,241
So, as you know, most in-app purchases menus

336
00:20:10,241 --> 00:20:12,264
do have multiple choices,

337
00:20:12,264 --> 00:20:14,667
where from the lowest to the highest.

338
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:17,771
What gets me, what really ruffles my

339
00:20:18,497 --> 00:20:23,898
feathers is when they automatically highlight the most expensive choice and make them animate or

340
00:20:23,898 --> 00:20:31,220
something and it's like $99 or something insane like that and children have been known to buy

341
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:39,882
these things because they have zero concept of in-app gem real world values. I'm not using the

342
00:20:39,882 --> 00:20:44,943
right terms but I think you know what I'm saying. The good thing about that is that that phenomenon

343
00:20:44,943 --> 00:20:47,503
has been curbed with actual laws like you know what

344
00:20:48,464 --> 00:20:51,605
Amazon or Apple, those platforms have been sued

345
00:20:51,605 --> 00:20:54,205
because they made it too easy for children

346
00:20:54,205 --> 00:20:58,926
to buy these things without any parental supervision.

347
00:20:58,926 --> 00:20:59,466
So, from a UX perspective,

348
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:03,227
we could have curbed that a little bit.

349
00:21:03,227 --> 00:21:08,769
I mean, just to make sure everything's balanced

350
00:21:08,769 --> 00:21:13,910
and to not prey on accidental purchases, basically.

351
00:21:16,227 --> 00:21:19,351
And the next one is definitive and clear language.

352
00:21:19,351 --> 00:21:19,411
So.

353
00:21:22,544 --> 00:21:26,567
Again, this one, players tend to have a mental model

354
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:32,231
of what they expect the UI to say or what the game does.

355
00:21:32,231 --> 00:21:36,274
And if your game or menu basically is very clear

356
00:21:36,274 --> 00:21:39,636
and very distinct about what's happening,

357
00:21:39,636 --> 00:21:41,097
they are less likely to be confused,

358
00:21:41,097 --> 00:21:42,999
they are less likely to be frustrated,

359
00:21:42,999 --> 00:21:46,721
and therefore they are less likely to have a bad experience.

360
00:21:46,721 --> 00:21:48,843
So as long as everything's clear,

361
00:21:48,843 --> 00:21:51,805
because I'm pretty sure there has been games

362
00:21:52,865 --> 00:21:57,886
they muddle up words, they use words that might sound like yes, might sound like no,

363
00:21:57,886 --> 00:22:02,047
but not quite, and just like, why is that? And you don't understand, and you kind of just click

364
00:22:02,047 --> 00:22:06,188
it anyway, and you end up somewhere you don't want to be. So therefore you get frustrated.

365
00:22:06,188 --> 00:22:12,569
So things like that is easily rectified with just clear language.

366
00:22:12,569 --> 00:22:13,589
This one is rewarding loyalty.

